The value of renewable energy is moving away from its generation, towards ‘when’ and ‘where’ it is delivered to the system/consumer. The analogue is the start of the 19th century oil industry when crude oil was ubiquitous and cheap and the economic value was in refining and distributing the product to market. Adaptogen Capital
